latestPosts.caption:
Men will say I’m just overthinking it…

But maybe we’re not all always overthinking and the standard is set by the under-thinkers that have never had to second-guess themselves (negative). 

Share this with a wrongfully accused overthinker and follow me for more femme rants 

#feminism #angryfeminist #overthinking

So much of the joy of parenting is in the smaller, fleeting, in-between moments that you don’t even end up recounting to anyone. It’s not always about a big milestone—sometimes true bliss is just doing cheers with your Costco Pizza underneath a redwood. I try so hard to remember to be grateful for these moments.
Sorry to all the people, bars, restaurants, museums, boats, trains and uber drivers that have been caught in our crossfire

“Does anyone have a curling iron?”
“Wait…WHAT time is it?”
“Can I put my dress in your bathroom while you shower”
“Can you do my contour”
“Shit the adapter fried the curler”
“Who needs another glass?”
“Is this cute to post?”

 bakbak > the actual dinner for me
Also…we did not make it at 8:30.
